name Amaretti Mousse
serves 4
tags dessert

# Preparation

- 200 ml espresso
- 20 g sugar
- 2 tbsp dark rum
- 75 g amaretti
Bring the espresso and sugar to a boil and reduce over low heat to ¼. Add the rum.
Crumble the amaretti and soak in the coffee-rum mixture.
-> soaked amaretti

- 100 g white couverture
@nodep
Chop and melt over a hot water bath.
-> couverture

- 4 sheets gelatine
@nodep
Soak in plenty of cold water.
-> gelatine

- 4 tbsp Amaretto
- 4 tbsp almond extract
- 1 egg
= couverture
= gelatine
Whisk the egg over a hot water bath until thick and creamy. Slowly fold in the couverture.
Warm the Amaretto and almond extract in a small pan, squeeze out the gelatine, dissolve in
the liquid and stir into the couverture-egg mixture. Leave to set slightly in the fridge
for 10-15 minutes.
-> amaretti cream

- 250 g whipping cream
- 2 egg whites
- 30 g sugar
@ amaretti cream
= soaked amaretti
<p>Whip the cream to soft peaks. Whisk the egg whites, gradually adding the sugar, until
the meringue is creamy and firm. Fold first the cream, then the meringue into the set
cream. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.</p>
<p>Carefully fold the soaked amaretti along with their liquid into the mousse using a
spatula. Refrigerate for 3-4 hours.</p>
